helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Sara Holzer, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9903
You can stop by the MSOE IT Helpdesk and drop it off at any time. Please make sure to bring the charger that was provided as well. At some point, a late fee will be assessed if we do not receive the unit. The Helpdesk is open Monday through Friday, from 8:00am to 4:30pm. As for the stickers, it would be much appreciated if you would remove them, but you are by no means required to remove them. I will be marking this issue resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Sara Holzer,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9903

You can stop by the MSOE IT Helpdesk and drop it off at any time. Please make sure to bring the charger that was provided as well. At some point, a late fee will be assessed if we do not receive the unit. The Helpdesk is open Monday through Friday, from 8:00am to 4:30pm. As for the stickers, it would be much appreciated if you would remove them, but you are by no means required to remove them. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mary Nielsen, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9943
Below I have attached instructions to change the default print setting to only print on one side of the paper. I will be marking this resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.
1) Select the Start Button in the bottom Left 2) Click on Devices and Printers 3) In the window that pops up, right click on the printer you want to change the setting for 4) Select Printing Preferences 5) In the window that appears, there should be a drop down labeled print type, click on it, and select 1-Sided 6) Click apply, and then close the window. Your printer will now default to one sided printing.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mary Nielsen,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9943

Below I have attached instructions to change the default print setting to only print on one side of the paper. I will be marking this resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.

1) Select the Start Button in the bottom Left
2) Click on Devices and Printers
3) In the window that pops up, right click on the printer you want to change the setting for
4) Select Printing Preferences
5) In the window that appears, there should be a drop down labeled print type, click on it, and select 1-Sided
6) Click apply, and then close the window. Your printer will now default to one sided printing.


Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Help with Jenzabar
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello Jasmine-
I am hoping you could help me do some troubleshooting in Jenzabar/PowerFAIDS.
We have a Configure Optional Student Data Elements to Transfer that we use to tell Jenzabar what information we need pulled from Jenzabar into PowerFAIDS.
In the past everything worked well. In the PowerFAIDS 21.3 update PowerFAIDS moved where the ACT score from Jenzabar is loading in. Since this change we have been update to get the ACT score into PowerFAIDs in any way. Even after multiple attempts to point it in the right direction and even deleting and re-added the information, we have been successful.
Could you please help me try to see if I am missing something?
Also, could we discuss more on the personalized XML file that can be used to bring over Jenzabar data into PowerFAIDS?
Thank you,
Heather

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Jasmine-
Yes, I am still having issues with the ACT coming over from Jenzabar into PowerFAIDS.
In the past as long as this line was checked it would be included in our Jenzabar interface file and would update a corresponding field in PowerFAIDS without issue. [cid:image001.jpg@01D1FDFC.C61C3BA0]
In the PowerFAIDS 21.3 upgrade PowerFAIDS moved the ACT field and renamed it to ACT Total. We verified that the ACT Total Score field was checked our Jenzabar interface file but that didn’t work. [cid:image002.jpg@01D1FDFC.C61C3BA0]
[cid:image003.jpg@01D1FDFC.C61C3BA0]
We then manually added our PowerFAIDS field to the Jenzabar interface file and got the same results. [cid:image004.jpg@01D1FDFC.C61C3BA0]
[cid:image003.jpg@01D1FDFC.C61C3BA0]
Please let me know if you have any other questions.
Thanks, Heather

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Help desk,
I am expecting to receive a Positive Pay file for payroll. Checks were issued yesterday. Why didn't the email have an attached file?
Thanks,
Kris
-----Original Message----- From: Jenzabar-MSOE [mailto:jenzabar@msoe.edu] Sent: Friday, August 05, 2016 12:10 AM To: Wesson, Kristine <wesson@msoe.edu>; Schwanebeck, Thomas <schwanebeck@msoe.edu>; Smith, Jo <smith@msoe.edu>; Database Team <databaseteam@msoe.edu> Subject: Payroll Checks - Positive Pay File
This is the Payroll Checks - Positive Pay File the next 24 hours
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Help desk,

I am expecting to receive a Positive Pay file for payroll. Checks were issued yesterday. Why didn't the email have an attached file?

Thanks,

Kris

-----Original Message-----
From: Jenzabar-MSOE [mailto:jenzabar@msoe.edu]
Sent: Friday, August 05, 2016 12:10 AM
To: Wesson, Kristine <wesson@msoe.edu>; Schwanebeck, Thomas <schwanebeck@msoe.edu>; Smith, Jo <smith@msoe.edu>; Database Team <databaseteam@msoe.edu>
Subject: Payroll Checks - Positive Pay File

This is the Payroll Checks - Positive Pay File the next 24 hours

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tracy/Kris,
For the last couple pay periods Kris hasn't received the positive pay file for payroll. We think this is because this paychecks are not run until the morning before payday (morning of the 4th when we get paid the 5th)
The file that Kris needs to send to the bank is based on a job that runs daily at 12:10am. This job looks ahead one day for paycheck data and if its there it will send it in csv file to Kris. Using this last pay period as an example when the job ran at 12:10am on the 4th it looked for paycheck date of the 5th but no data was there because paychecks were not run until the morning of the 4th. The job will run again at 12:10am on the 5th but it will be looking for a check date of the 6th so no file will be created.
When we created this job we made the assumption that paychecks would be run by end of day on the 3rd. That way when the job runs at 12:10am on the 4th there would be data there to create the csv file Kris needs to send to the bank.
To make sure that Kris receives the file she needs we are proposing that we change the time the job runs. Instead of 12:10am daily we'd like to run it at 3pm daily. Tracy on a normal pay period is it safe to say that paychecks will be done by 3pm the day before payday? Kris if you get the file at 3pm the day before payday does that give you enough time to get it to the bank.
Kris, the only flaw we see with this is Monday and holiday weeks. Most likely you will receive the file on your day off. The other option is to schedule the job so you get the file on payday at 6am.
Let us know what you think
Thanks Jasmine & Mike Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9960 Help desk, I am expecting to receive a Positive Pay file for payroll. Checks were issued yesterday. Why didn't the email have an attached file? helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Tracy/Kris,

For the last couple pay periods Kris hasn't received the positive pay file for payroll.  We think this is because this paychecks are not run until the morning before payday (morning of the 4th when we get paid the 5th)

The file that Kris needs to send to the bank is based on a job that runs daily at 12:10am.  This job looks ahead one day for paycheck data and if its there it will send it in csv file to Kris.  Using this last pay period as an example when the job ran at 12:10am on the 4th it looked for paycheck date of the 5th but no data was there because paychecks were not run until the morning of the 4th.  The job will run again at 12:10am on the 5th but it will be looking for a check date of the 6th so no file will be created. 

When we created this job we made the assumption that paychecks would be run by end of day on the 3rd.  That way when the job runs at 12:10am on the 4th there would be data there to create the csv file Kris needs to send to the bank. 

To make sure that Kris receives the file she needs we are proposing that we change the time the job runs.  Instead of 12:10am daily we'd like to run it at 3pm daily.  Tracy on a normal pay period is it safe to say that paychecks will be done by 3pm the day before payday?  Kris if you get the file at 3pm the day before payday does that give  you enough time to get it to the bank.

Kris, the only flaw we see with this is Monday and holiday weeks.  Most likely you will receive the file on your day off.  The other option is to schedule the job so you get the file on payday at 6am.

helpdesk-note.body:
I agree with Kris that 11am would probably be better. My only concern is that payroll checks will not always be created the day before payroll. Payroll on 7/20 had a one day turnaround so that is why the checks were not printed until the day before payroll. On this last payroll I did have a bit more time, but there was quite a bit of payroll data to process so it took me longer than normal. Because I was here until after 6pm on the 3rd, I only sent the file to the bank and to Kris so that the bank would have the information but waited until the next morning to run the checks. On a “normal” payroll run this would all be done 2 days before payroll. So my concern is that if we change the date for the positive pay information to pull, what happens if the checks are run two days before? At what step is the positive pay file generated – is it only after I run the Infomaker report to print the checks? Check numbers are assigned during the previous payroll step so I just want to make sure I am understanding the process correctly.
Tracy

The file that Kris needs to send to the bank is based on a job that runs daily at 12:10am.  This job looks ahead one day for paycheck data and if its there it will send it in csv file to Kris.  Using this last pay period as an example when the job ran at 12:10am on the 4th it looked for paycheck date of the 5th but no data was there because paychecks were not run until the morning of the 4th.  The job will run again at 12:10am on the 5th but it will be looking for a check date of the 6th so no file will be created. 
 
When we created this job we made the assumption that paychecks would be run by end of day on the 3rd.  That way when the job runs at 12:10am on the 4th there would be data there to create the csv file Kris needs to send to the bank. 
 
To make sure that Kris receives the file she needs we are proposing that we change the time the job runs.  Instead of 12:10am daily we'd like to run it at 3pm daily.  Tracy on a normal pay period is it safe to say that paychecks will be done by 3pm the day before payday?  Kris if you get the file at 3pm the day before payday does that give  you enough time to get it to the bank.
 
Kris, the only flaw we see with this is Monday and holiday weeks.  Most likely you will receive the file on your day off.  The other option is to schedule the job so you get the file on payday at 6am. 
 
Let us know what you think
 
Thanks
Jasmine & Mike

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Allison,
We most certainly can print that poster for you. Our poster plotter has a maximum width of 36", which is fine because one of your sides is under 36. However, there will be approximately 6" of white space on the side of the poster that is 30".
Feel free to email the poster to Helpdesk@msoe.edu or you can always bring it in to the desk. Printing takes about 10 minutes, depending on how busy we are.
Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Password reset
helpdesk-ticket.description:
This ticket is being created because you requested a password reset by calling the MSOE IT Helpdesk at 414-277-7288. We are always happy to reset passwords for our users. However, sometimes the Helpdesk is not open when you need your password reset. Luckily we have a password reset page available to all of our users.
If it is your first time resetting your password online, please go to pwdreg.msoe.edu and follow the instructions for registering your password.
If you have already registered your password, please go to pwd.msoe.edu and reset it manually.
Have a great day!

On Mon, 8 Aug at 5:59 pm , Jerri <jerridelgado11@gmail.com> wrote:
I set up my email and entered a password, through that I had to confirm my email which I did and then it told me to confirm my password which I did and then it told me to log in so I clicked the log in and it sent me to the log in page which was the adfs msoe web title. I couldn't log in on that screen. I tried multiple times and I tried going through the whole process again but it wouldn't let me.
[#INC-9983]

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jerri:
You are set for login. We re-set your password and I was able to login as you. The only configuration I did was to set your status as a prospective MSOE student.
When you go back to the website, your login name is your email address, and the password is "Summer2016" (without the quotes).
When you login, you'll be on a landing page with four big pictuires that represent communities you can visit on the site. At the top of the screen, you'll see your name and a blue dot next to it. The blue dot means you have a message waiting, so you can click the dot and go read it. It's probably a generic welcome message.
Next, click your name and you'll get a drop-down list of things you can do - I recommend the first thing is to go to your profile and edit it. You can put as much or as little info about yourself in there as you want, and add a photo (this is optional).
Finally, I want to point out the menu bar - look for the link at far left to "My News." That will show you some of the latest things posted to the Community.
From here you can access the online application.
Good luck, and please let me know if you run into difficulty or have any questions.
Kent Peterson MSOE Marketing and Public Affairs peterson@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description: My "my.msoe" account is not active due to leaving msoe and coming back before two years, along with my email address. I will not be on campus until 5pm on 9/6 due to working full time. Please feel free to call or email me so we can get this set up. Cora
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
My "my.msoe" account is not active due to leaving msoe and coming back before two years, along with my email address. I will not be on campus until 5pm on 9/6 due to working full time. Please feel free to call or email me so we can get this set up.

Cora

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Cora,
Accounts are created automatically when a student is registered for courses. So all that you need to do in order to create an account is contact the Registrar or your advisor so that you can register for courses.
However, it looks like you actually already have an account created. You may just not know the password? The default password for MSOE accounts follows the pattern: Msoe + ID number + Birthday. So it will look something like Msoe######MMDDYY
If you are still unable to log in with that password please respond to this ticket and we can walk you through resetting your password.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Cora,

Accounts are created automatically when a student is registered for courses. So all that you need to do in order to create an account is contact the Registrar or your advisor so that you can register for courses. 

However, it looks like you actually already have an account created. You may just not know the password? 
The default password for MSOE accounts follows the pattern: Msoe + ID number + Birthday. So it will look something like Msoe######MMDDYY

If you are still unable to log in with that password please respond to this ticket and we can walk you through resetting your password.

Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Dear Help Desk,
I am unable to use the Global Connect VPN with my new ZBook on Windows 10. Here are the settings I applied: [cid:image001.jpg@01D1F1B3.6A05F3B0]
Can you please advise?
Thanks,
Mike Sracic
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Dear Help Desk,
 
I am unable to use the Global Connect VPN with my new ZBook on Windows 10. Here are the settings I applied:
 
Can you please advise?
 
Thanks,

Mike Sracic

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Mike,
Our apologies that you are unable to connect to Global Protect.
So you have mostly the correct settings...
The Portal used is sslvpn.msoe.edu which looks to be correct. You username is simply your msoe username, which also looks correct. Obviously you need to enter your MSOE password into the password field. Once all of that is entered into the corresponding fields, please tab Apply and then let it sit for ~40 seconds. It may say "Resend credential" but please ignore that until after the 40 second wait. This should let you connect.
Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Internet Connection at Grohmann Towers
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello, I just wanted to submit a ticket to say that I have been trying to use my internet tonight since 7pm. The internet speed has been around 5Mb/s and the ping has been at a consistent 300ms the whole time. In terms of what we should expect from our internet this isn't even close. Is there any explanation for this and/or how soon can it be expected to be stable again here at the Grohmann Towers? Thanks, Riley Bruce
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,

I just wanted to submit a ticket to say that I have been trying to use my internet tonight since 7pm. The internet speed has been around 5Mb/s and the ping has been at a consistent 300ms the whole time. In terms of what we should expect from our internet this isn't even close. Is there any explanation for this and/or how soon can it be expected to be stable again here at the Grohmann Towers?

Thanks,
Riley Bruce

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Riley,
Thanks for the speed information. Would you mind providing a little more information, such as: Which floor are you on? Are multiple devices experiencing these speeds? Are you experiencing this on the wired, or wireless, or both? And do you have any devices between yours and the wall port, such as routers, switches, or hubs? Thank you. helpdesk-note.body: So I tried restarting router, restarting my computer, and troubleshooting my network card. My ping was good for about 2 hours today but it is back to a consistent 200 right now..
helpdesk-note.body-html: So I tried restarting router, restarting my computer, and troubleshooting my network card. My ping was good for about 2 hours today but it is back to a consistent 200 right now..

helpdesk-note.body: What I'm noticing is it is just very inconsistent with the ping. It will spike all the way up to 250-300ms but be as low as 10-30 at other times. I have the TP-Link N900 network card for my computer and the Nighthawk is on the other side of the wall. I just was wondering if there is anything going on or if there is something I can do to mitigate how inconsistent my ping is from day to day, because not knowing what my ping will be makes gaming pretty difficult.

If you could pull it off the network and test your pings through either the provided wired or wireless and let me know the results, I would greatly appreciate it.
Thank you!

helpdesk-note.body: Sam, This frustration is not directed at you, but more the Grohmann Tower setup as a whole. The reason I even use a network card for my desktop computer is that we have one Ethernet port that is usable in my 12th floor apartment. Therefore we have one router that is hooked up to it and runs everything. I can understand how the router may seem like an issue and bypassing it and testing might show different results, but it makes no difference as that setup will not work in the future. The point I'm making is that my setup has not changed for an entire year and I have not had issues until about 2 weeks ago and the issue persists today. So it is not feasible to take the router off and run an Ethernet cable to my desktop which is in an entirely different room. -Riley

Thank you!
Sam

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Turnitin Plagiarism Prevention FY2017 Subscription Renewal
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello Support, For a number of years, the library annually subscribed to the Turnitin Plagiarism Prevention service. A few years ago, the IT Department assumed responsibility for processing the renewal paperwork, including the financial paperwork, for this subscription. Pat Hurlbut assumed responsibility for serving as the account administrator for MSOE. Late yesterday, I was contacted by Turnitin regarding MSOE's Turnitin renewal. The Turnitin account manager, Krishana Anderson, had reached out to Pat Hurlbut several times regarding our renewal. Krishana finally learned that Pat Hurlbut is no longer here at MSOE, so Krishana contacted me and e-mailed me our Turnitin Subscription Renewal Form. I have attached the Renewal Form. We would like to renew the Turnitin subscription. Several MSOE faculty use Turnitin. In order to renew the subscription, the Renewal Form needs to be completed and returned to Krishana Anderson at Turnitin (kanderson@turnitin.com). The Renewal Form can be used to generate a requisition in Jenzabar. I'm assuming that after the Renewal Form is returned to Turnitin, they will issue an invoice, and the invoice number can be included on the MSOE purchase order. In addition to completing the renewal, Turnitin also needs to know who will serve as MSOE's account administrator. MSOE's current subscription ends on August 15. The renewal needs to be processed as soon as possible. Can someone in IT process this renewal as soon as possible? Can someone in IT serve as the account administrator? Please let me know. Thanks very much, Gary Shimek Director of the Library
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello Support,

For a number of years, the library annually subscribed to the Turnitin Plagiarism Prevention service.  A few years ago, the IT Department assumed responsibility for processing the renewal paperwork, including the financial paperwork, for this subscription.  Pat Hurlbut assumed responsibility for serving as the account administrator for MSOE. 

Late yesterday, I was contacted by Turnitin regarding MSOE's Turnitin renewal.  The Turnitin account manager, Krishana Anderson, had reached out to Pat Hurlbut several times regarding our renewal.  Krishana finally learned that Pat Hurlbut is no longer here at MSOE, so Krishana contacted me and e-mailed me our Turnitin Subscription Renewal Form. 

I have attached the Renewal Form.

We would like to renew the Turnitin subscription.  Several MSOE faculty use Turnitin. 

In order to renew the subscription, the Renewal Form needs to be completed and returned to Krishana Anderson at Turnitin (kanderson@turnitin.com).  The Renewal Form can be used to generate a requisition in Jenzabar. I'm assuming that after the Renewal Form is returned to Turnitin, they will issue an invoice, and the invoice number can be included on the MSOE purchase order. 

In addition to completing the renewal, Turnitin also needs to know who will serve as MSOE's account administrator. 

MSOE's current subscription ends on August 15.  The renewal needs to be processed as soon as possible. 

Can someone in IT process this renewal as soon as possible?  Can someone in IT serve as the account administrator? 

Please let me know.

Thanks very much,

Gary Shimek
Director of the Library

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Betty,
I am emailing you to let you know that Dr. Meier's class should be able to install MatLab2016a now. The steps for doing so are: 1) Open up the start menu. 2) Search "Software Center" 3) Within Software Center Search within Applications and select Matlab2016a. 4) Click Install 5) After installation there is a bug that says it has failed, reboot the machine and the status should change to success.
That should be about all the important information Dr. Meier Needs for his class. Feel free to forward this to him and whoever else needs it. If there are any other questions or concerns please let me know. Have a nice day Betty :)

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Accessing Webex
helpdesk-ticket.description: Good morning! I want to set up a Webex meeting, and I was informed that we have a Webex account through MSOE. However, I can't find any information as to where to login to our account. Would you be able to forward instructions or the login location to me? Thank you!
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Good morning!  I want to set up a Webex meeting, and I was informed that we have a Webex account through MSOE.  However, I can't find any information as to where to login to our account.  Would you be able to forward instructions or the login location to me?  Thank you!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jennifer Abing, I just activated your account on the webex server. It should send you instructions but if not it fairly easy to use once you know that the server is located at meeting.msoe.edu. Log in with your normal work email and password. There will be a client you can preinstall, but you don't have to, it will load the first time you join a meeting and only takes a minute. There is an integration tool for outlook that allows you to allocate server time to your meeting created in outlook and it will attach all the webex info to your meeting invite, but most people don't webex enough to worry about installing it.
Let me know if you need more help, Tony

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi shibilski, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10057
The group policy has now been changed so that you will be able to run the macros you require. To ensure that you are able to please follow the steps below. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.
1) Click the Windows Key and the R Key 2) Type cmd and hit enter
3) In the window that appears type gpupdate /force
If prompted, log off and/or restart the computer.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi shibilski,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10057

The group policy has now been changed so that you will be able to run the macros you require. To ensure that you are able to please follow the steps below. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.

1) Click the Windows Key and the R Key
2) Type cmd and hit enter
3) In the window that appears type gpupdate /force

If prompted, log off and/or restart the computer.

Thanks,
Thomas Schleich

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Catherine, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10061 The large monitor/computer in R103 would not open a powerpoint without entering an email or product code. We were not sure what to enter. This has not been needed previously.
The Mondopad in the room does not have an account in Office so the Office applications will require a log in. The solution to this issue is to use your own laptop connected to the Mondopad for Office applications.
Plug in via VGA or HDMI cable. Push the input button on the side of the mondopad until it is on the input method you just used to connect. win-p to select your projection preference, duplicate in most cases. Use Power Point or any application on your laptop.
With this information, I will consider this issue resolved. If trouble persists or there are problems with the instruction set, please respond to this incident and it will reopen for my team to investigate. Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Catherine,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10061
The large monitor/computer in R103 would not open a powerpoint without entering an email or product code. We were not sure what to enter. This has not been needed previously. 

The Mondopad in the room does not have an account in Office so the Office applications will require a log in.  The solution to this issue is to use your own laptop connected to the Mondopad for Office applications.

Plug in via VGA or HDMI cable.
Push the input button on the side of the mondopad until it is on the input method you just used to  connect.
win-p to select your projection preference, duplicate in most cases.
Use Power Point or any application on your laptop.

With this information, I will consider this issue resolved.  If trouble persists or there are problems with the instruction set, please respond to this incident and it will reopen for my team to investigate.

Peter Pfister

helpdesk-note.body:
After the power outages in the dorms, it looks like several of the alarm/PA switches did not recover. We still haven't determined who supports these. The problem is that they are a Rob Job and are one-offs and not part of our network infrastructure. In the future, I'd like to make the alarm net and PA part of MSOE network, so we know when they are down, and so they will suck less.
We can plan to reboot these tomorrow.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: question about Grohman Tower internet, open NAT?
helpdesk-ticket.description: is it an open NAT in Grohmann towers? If not, is there anyway to get one? will be moving into 909 in about a week. Uses xboxOne to communicate with family and friends in Texas while at school.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: is it an open NAT in Grohmann towers?  If not, is there anyway to get one?  will be moving into 909 in about a week.  Uses xboxOne to communicate with family and friends in Texas while at school.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Adam,
MSOE does not use NAT at this time. All IP addresses are internet-routable, and are not translated IP addresses. The IP you get when connecting to our network is the one that people outside our network see. You will only have a NAT if you are using a router or switch that provides DHCP other than the DHCP provided by MSOE.
That being said, I am familiar with what XBO considers NAT. The reason you may see errors along the line of "Can't get a Teredo IP address" is indicating that XBO did not get and cannot see an IPv6 network. MSOE blocks all IPv6 traffic as our servers, routers, and firewalls do not have policies in place to manage IPv6 traffic. All IPv6 traffic will revert to IPv4 if it cannot establish a connection. Use of IPv6 or IPv4 will not impact your network experience.
There are some steps you can take if you are using a router or switch between your device and our network. You can forward ports on your router to the IP address of your XBO. This will require giving the XBO a static IP address. You can also place your XBO in the DMZ of the route. This will also require a static IP, but is less effort than setting up port forwarding. This puts your XBO outside of the security provided by your router.
MSOE provides internet to students as best we can, while not sacrificing the safety or experience of other users. You may not get an Open NAT while on our network for the reasons above, as well as others. This should not impact the speed and quality of your gaming experience, but it may prevent you from hosting in some of your games.
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_address_translation http://support.xbox.com/en-US/xbox-one/networking/network-ports-used-xbox-live
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu
(414) 277-2355
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10088
is it an open NAT in Grohmann towers? If not, is there anyway to get one? will be moving into 909 in about a week. Uses xboxOne to communicate with family and friends in Texas while at school.

You will only have a NAT if you are using a router or switch that provides DHCP other than the DHCP provided by MSOE.

That being said, I am familiar with what XBO considers NAT. The reason you may see errors along the line of "Can't get a Teredo IP address" is indicating that XBO did not get and cannot see an IPv6 network. MSOE blocks all IPv6 traffic as our servers, routers, and firewalls do not have policies in place to manage IPv6 traffic. All IPv6 traffic will revert to IPv4 if it cannot establish a connection. Use of IPv6 or IPv4 will not impact your network experience.

There are some steps you can take if you are using a router or switch between your device and our network. You can forward ports on your router to the IP address of your XBO. This will require giving the XBO a static IP address. You can also place your XBO in the DMZ of the route. This will also require a static IP, but is less effort than setting up port forwarding. This puts your XBO outside of the security provided by your router.

helpdesk-note.body:

If you are using Skype to communicate, Skype will use any available port to communicate. It should reliably find an unused port. helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: EES Academic version for 2016-17 (2nd notice)
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I received the following e-mail from F-Chart, the makers of the EES software used in the BE and possibly the ME programs. We need to download and configure a new version of this software for the coming academic year (the version we have expires on August 31. Our license number (needed to complete the update instructions below) is #4026. According to my records Michael Timm dealt with this last year, so he would probably be the best person to do it this year.
From: F-Chart Software [mailto:info=fchart.com@mail213.atl171.mcdlv.net] On Behalf Of F-Chart Software Sent: Wednesday, August 10, 2016 8:06 PM To: Tritt, Dr. Charles <tritt@msoe.edu> Subject: EES Academic version for 2016-17 (2nd notice)
Dear EES Administrator, You should have received the annual EES Academic update notice at the end of July, but our records indicate that your EES license has not yet been renewed. The process becomes more difficult if you wait until after September 1st. We recommend that you download it now. You will need to use the new password.
Below is a copy of the instructions that were sent in July. Please ignore this message if you have successfully completed the annual renewal.
[https://gallery.mailchimp.com/2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0/images/47d8dca1-3c9c-4a5b-bd86-9e8989f10914.gif]
F-Chart Software, LLC
P.O.Box 44042
Madison, WI 53744 USA
608-274-4262 ph/fax
info@fchart.com<mailto:info@fchart.com>
http://fchart.com<http://fchart.us13.list-manage2.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=7fc95e6c63&e=5262e8ab73>
Update Instructions for the Academic Versions of EES (2016-17)
Please read these instructions carefully as the update process has changed from that used in previous years.
You are receiving this message because our records indicate that you are the administrator of the Academic EES license for your department. If you no longer are the administrator, or if you plan to transfer your responsibility to another person, please inform us by e-mail to info@fchart.com<mailto:info@fchart.com>. Doing so will ensure that your department receives updates in the future.
You MUST update EES before midnight, August 31, 2016 or your existing version of EES will expire. If you do not update before this date, you will not be able to use any version of EES, new or old. If this happens, see the Special Instructions for Expired Versions below.
This message provides instructions to download the new Academic version of EES. There is no cost to update an Academic license. Do not distribute this message, login name or password to anyone. Access to our server is intended only for EES administrators. Do not provide the download information to students or other faculty as this may result in blocking access to our website.
NOTE: There are both 32-bit and 64-bit Academic EES programs. Most of the existing Academic licenses are for the 32-bit Commercial or Professional versions, which are designed to work on both 32 and 64-bit Microsoft Windows operating systems. The 64-bit Academic Professional version requires an optional 64-bit EES license file (EES.dft64). If your department has not purchased this license file, you will not be able to use the 64-bit version. The 64-bit program is only provided as a Professional Academic version. (There is no 64-bit Commercial version.). See http://www.fchart.com/ees/64-bit.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=8a1059e22f&e=5262e8ab73> for more information about the 64-bit version. Separate directions follow for the 32-bit (Commercial & Professional versions) and for the 64-bit Professional version.
Downloading and Installing the 32-bit Commercial or Professional EES Version Using your internet browser program, go to http://fchart.com<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=35868b5f2e&e=5262e8ab73>. Click on the "EES Instant Update" link at the right of the page to bring up the EES Instant Update & Technical Service (IUTS) page. Then click on the orange Download Latest EES button and enter the following information in the EES Instant Update Login screen.
Login Name: EES_XXXX Password: d1EESel Email: administrator email address
You must replace XXXX in the above login name with your 4-digit EES license number. This number is displayed in the first window that appears when EES is started. It is also provided on the receipt that was emailed to you when the program was purchased. Note that the password has the number 1 for the second character and the lower case letter L for the last character.
After entering the login information, you will be able to download Setup_EES_Acad.exe. EES is designed to operate on computers running the 32 or 64-bit Microsoft Vista, XP, and Windows 7/8/10 operating systems. (There is no Macintosh version See http://www.fchart.com/ees/mac-linux.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=71b1d65ced&e=5262e8ab73> for options regarding the use of EES on Macintosh computers.) Run the Setup_EES_Acad.exe file to install the new version. You will be prompted to select a directory in which the EES program will be installed. We recommend that you install the program into your existing EES folder. If you install EES into a different folder, you will need to copy the EES.dft file from your current EES folder into the folder where the new version has been placed. After installation, start EES and ensure that the expiration date displayed on the startup screen is 9/01/2017. Keep these instructions and periodically check our server to see if a new version of EES is available. We often provide updates during the year.
Downloading and Installing the 64-bit Academic Professional EES Version Use these directions only if your department has purchased the EES 64-bit license file.
Using your internet browser program, go to http://fchart.com<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=0b9d9ca154&e=5262e8ab73>. Click on the "EES Instant Update" link at the right of the page to bring up the EES Instant Update & Technical Service (IUTS) page. Then click on the orange Download Latest EES button and enter the following information in the EES Instant Update Login screen.
Login Name: EES64_XXXX Password: d1EESel Email: administrator email address
You must replace XXXX in the above login name with your 4-digit EES license number. This number is displayed in the first window that appears when EES64 is started. It is also provided on the receipt that was emailed to you when the program was purchased. Note that the password has the number 1 for the second character and the lower case letter L for the last character.
After entering the login information, you will be able to download Setup_EES64_Acad.exe. EES64 is designed to operate on computers running Microsoft Windows 7/8/10 64-bit operating systems. Run the Setup_EES64_Acad.exe file to install the new version. You will be prompted to select a directory in which the EES64 program will be installed. We recommend that you install the program into your existing EES64 folder. If you install into a different folder, you will need to copy the EES.dft64 file from your current EES64 folder into the folder where the new version has been placed. After installation, start EES64 and ensure that the expiration date displayed on the startup screen is 9/01/2017. Keep these instructions and periodically check our server to see if a new version of EES64 is available. We often provide updates during the year.
File Distribution The Academic license agreement allows the setup and license files and the EES manual (EES_MANUAL.pdf) to be made available to colleagues and students in your department and to your network systems administrator for installation on your network, if necessary. You may place these files on a server for access by students and faculty in your department. However, the setup and license files must not be made available to anyone outside of your department. If you place the EES setup file, EES application or license file on a server, you must ensure that no one outside of your students and faculty in your department can access the files. Failure to meet this or other requirements of our End User License Agreement (http://fchart.com/ees/eula.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=cfeaa9395d&e=5262e8ab73>) will result in suspension of your EES license. Please take care to ensure that you and your users do not put the Setup_EES_Acad.exe, Setup_EES64_Acad.exe, EES.dft or EES.dft64 files on an internet site or make them available to persons outside of your department, as this will also cause a suspension of your license.
Special Instructions for Expired Versions If EES displays the expiration notice, you may be able to recover use of the program as follows: First, download and install the 2016-17 version into your existing EES directory, as explained above. Then replace the license (EES.dft or EES.dft64) file with one that has not displayed the "expired" message. You may be able to find one on a computer that has not been used to run EES after August 31. If you cannot find a valid copy of the license file, it will be necessary to purchase a new license file ($100, credit card payment only) from our website on page http://fchart.com/ees/order.php. A purchase order or bank wire transfer will not be accepted for a replacement license file.
Correcting EES Installation Problems
1. If the expired message appears, first ensure that you have installed the 2016-17 version as described above. The start-up screen should briefly display the version and expiration data before the program closes. If the 2016-17 version is installed, check to ensure that your computer clock is displaying the correct date. Correct the date if necessary. After the expiration message has been displayed it is necessary to replace the EES.dft (or EES.dft64) file. 2. If an error occurs while the 32-bit version of EES is starting, the problem may be caused by a video driver that is incompatible the EES 3D plotting capability. If this problem occurs, reinstall EES, but this time, be sure to uncheck the Install 3D plotting capability box. 3. Contact F-Chart Software at info@fchart.com<mailto:info@fchart.com> for any other problems. Attach a copy of the EES license file (EES.dft) and the EES file that is causing a problem.
New Features and EESy Solutions Newsletter A short description of the new features in EES can be seen by selecting the New Features menu item in the Help menu of the new version or from http://fchart.com/ees/new-features.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=4a756d6b99&e=5262e8ab73>. Note that only new features are listed here. There have been many minor changes and bug fixes and these are not reported. You may also wish to download recent issues of the EESy Solutions Newsletter (http://fchart.com/ees/eesy-solutions-newsletter.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=0cfac3a69b&e=5262e8ab73>) which describes some of the new features as well as providing tips on using EES.
Component Library The Component Library is the newest application library provided, joining the Heat Transfer and Mechanical Design libraries. This library is only available in the 32 and 64-bit Professional versions. The Component Library provides access to a set of EES functions and procedures that simulate components in thermal-fluid systems. Currently there component models for Combustors, Compressors, Turbines, Fans & Blowers, Pumps, Heat Exchangers, Heat & Mass Exchangers, Nozzles & Diffusers, and Flow Control Devices. The use of the Component Library enables the user to quickly develop system models with fewer system level convergence issues.
Manual The latest EES manual can be downloaded from the EES Manual link at the lower right of page http://fchart.com/ees/. Right click on this link and select Save Link As... to download the manual as a .PDF file. You need Adobe Acrobat to read the PDF file - a free copy of Adobe Acrobat is available from http://www.adobe.com/. If you copy the EES_Manual.PDF file into the folder in which EES is installed, it will be accessible from the EES Help menu.
Mastering EES Book Mastering EES<http://fchart.us13.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=27ebce5a58&e=5262e8ab73> is a 775 page book written by S.A. Klein and G.F. Nellis that provides a comprehensive presentation of all of the features in the Commercial and Professional versions of EES. Mastering EES differs from the EES manual in its organization, reading style and detail. It also provides many more examples than the manual. The book is intended both for those who have never used EES as well as for advanced users. It is available as an electronic download in .PDF format for $25 from http:\\fchart.com<http://fchart.us13.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=be52da27a6&e=5262e8ab73> for a single-user copy. A purchase of five versions ($125) allows the ebook to be posted on your network so that it is accessible for all users in your department. If you copy Mastering_EES.pdf into the EES directory, it can be accessed from the Mastering EES menu item in the Help menu without having to enter a password. Also, when accessed from the Mastering EES menu, EES will provide an option to download the latest copy.
Upgrades There are two versions of the 32-bit EES Academic license: Commercial and Professional. The additional capabilities provided by the Professional version are listed on our web site at: http://fchart.com/ees/pro-comm-versions.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=8f979a989f&e=5262e8ab73>. As noted above, the Component Library is available in the Professional version. You may update an Academic Commercial license to an Academic Professional license at any time by contacting F-Chart Software at info@fchart.com<mailto:info@fchart.com>. You will receive full credit for the original license payment. The 32-bit Academic Professional version can be further upgraded to the 64-bit Academic Professional version by purchase of the 64-bit license file ($750). The purchase can be made directly from our website (http://www.fchart.com/ees/order.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=8041843643&e=5262e8ab73>) or with a purchase order submitted to info@fchart.com<mailto:info@fchart.com>. See http://fchart.com/ees/64-bit.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=45277c5664&e=5262e8ab73> for information about the 64-bit version of EES.
Heat Transfer Textbook and Library An extensive library of functions useful for solving heat transfer problems is included with all academic versions of EES. This library has been extended with additional heat transfer correlations and also provides correlations for fluid flow minor losses and measurement. Select Function Information (Options menu) and click on the Heat Transfer radio button to view these functions. Detailed help files including examples are provided with these functions. The heat transfer library was developed to accompany the book: Heat Transfer G.F. Nellis and S.A. Klein Cambridge University Press, 2009 ISBN 978-0-521-88107-4 http://www.cambridge.org/us/engineering/author/nellisandklein/<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=4b3cfb9dfb&e=5262e8ab73> Example problems can be downloaded from http://fchart.com/ees/books.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage2.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=47ae26d427&e=5262e8ab73>
Thermodynamics Textbook EES was originally developed for use in thermodynamics courses. A thermodynamics textbook written by S.A. Klein (the author of EES) and colleague G.F. Nellis was published in 2012. This book is tightly integrated with EES and it provides detailed instruction relating to solving thermodynamics problems using EES and many advanced examples and interesting problems. Thermodynamics S.A. Klein and G.F. Nellis Cambridge University Press, 2012 ISBN 978-0-521-19570-6 http://www.cambridge.org/us/thermodynamics/<http://fchart.us13.list-manage2.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=efbffe3784&e=5262e8ab73> Example problems can be downloaded from http://fchart.com/ees/books.php<http://fchart.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=2bc6ee354c5ccea71800437a0&id=960427e226&e=5262e8ab73>

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I received the following e-mail from F-Chart, the makers of the EES software used in the BE and possibly the ME programs. We need to download and configure a new version of this software for the coming academic year (the version we have expires on August 31. Our license number (needed to complete the update instructions below) is #4026. According to my records Michael Timm dealt with this last year, so he would probably be the best person to do it this year.
 
From: F-Chart Software [mailto:info=fchart.com@mail213.atl171.mcdlv.net] On Behalf Of F-Chart Software
Sent: Wednesday, August 10, 2016 8:06 PM
To: Tritt, Dr. Charles <tritt@msoe.edu>
Subject: EES Academic version for 2016-17 (2nd notice)
 
Dear EES Administrator,
You should have received the annual EES Academic update notice at the end of July, but our records indicate that your EES license has not yet been renewed. The process becomes more difficult if you wait until after September 1st.  We recommend that you download it now.  You will need to use the new password. 

Below is a copy of the instructions that were sent in July.  Please ignore this message if you have successfully completed the annual renewal.
 
 
F-Chart Software, LLC
P.O.Box 44042
Madison, WI 53744 USA
608-274-4262 ph/fax
info@fchart.com
http://fchart.com
 
 

Update Instructions for the Academic Versions of EES (2016-17)
 
Please read these instructions carefully as the update process has changed from that used in previous years. 
 
You are receiving this message because our records indicate that you are the administrator of the Academic EES license for your department.  If you no longer are the administrator, or if you plan to transfer your responsibility to another person, please inform us by e-mail to info@fchart.com.  Doing so will ensure that your department receives updates in the future.
 
You MUST update EES before midnight, August 31, 2016 or your existing version of EES will expire.  If you do not update before this date, you will not be able to use any version of EES, new or old.  If this happens, see the Special Instructions for Expired Versions below.
 
This message provides instructions to download the new Academic version of EES.  There is no cost to update an Academic license.  Do not distribute this message, login name or password to anyone.  Access to our server is intended only for EES administrators.  Do not provide the download information to students or other faculty as this may result in blocking access to our website. 
 
NOTE:  There are both 32-bit and 64-bit Academic EES programs. Most of the existing Academic licenses are for the 32-bit Commercial or Professional versions, which are designed to work on both 32 and 64-bit Microsoft Windows operating systems.  The 64-bit Academic Professional version requires an optional 64-bit EES license file (EES.dft64).  If your department has not purchased this license file, you will not be able to use the 64-bit version.  The 64-bit program is only provided as a Professional Academic version.  (There is no 64-bit Commercial version.).  See http://www.fchart.com/ees/64-bit.php for more information about the 64-bit version.  Separate directions follow for the 32-bit (Commercial & Professional versions) and for the 64-bit Professional version.
 
Downloading and Installing the 32-bit Commercial or Professional EES Version
Using your internet browser program, go to http://fchart.com.  Click on the "EES Instant Update" link at the right of the page to bring up the EES Instant Update & Technical Service (IUTS) page.  Then click on the orange Download Latest EES button and enter the following information in the EES Instant Update Login screen.
 
Login Name: EES_XXXX
Password: d1EESel
Email: administrator email address
 
You must replace XXXX in the above login name with your 4-digit EES license number.  This number is displayed in the first window that appears when EES is started.  It is also provided on the receipt that was emailed to you when the program was purchased.  Note that the password has the number 1 for the second character and the lower case letter L for the last character.
 
After entering the login information, you will be able to download Setup_EES_Acad.exe.  EES is designed to operate on computers running the 32 or 64-bit Microsoft Vista, XP, and Windows  7/8/10 operating systems.  (There is no Macintosh version  See http://www.fchart.com/ees/mac-linux.php for options regarding the use of EES on Macintosh computers.)  Run the Setup_EES_Acad.exe file to install the new version.  You will be prompted to select a directory in which the EES program will be installed.  We recommend that you install the program into your existing EES folder.  If you install EES into a different folder, you will need to copy the EES.dft file from your current EES folder into the folder where the new version has been placed.  After installation, start EES and ensure that the expiration date displayed on the startup screen is 9/01/2017.  Keep these instructions and periodically check our server to see if a new version of EES is available.  We often provide updates during the year.
 
Downloading and Installing the 64-bit Academic Professional EES Version
Use these directions only if your department has purchased the EES 64-bit license file.

Using your internet browser program, go to http://fchart.com.  Click on the "EES Instant Update" link at the right of the page to bring up the EES Instant Update & Technical Service (IUTS) page.  Then click on the orange Download Latest EES button and enter the following information in the EES Instant Update Login screen.
 
Login Name: EES64_XXXX
Password: d1EESel
Email: administrator email address
 
You must replace XXXX in the above login name with your 4-digit EES license number.  This number is displayed in the first window that appears when EES64 is started.  It is also provided on the receipt that was emailed to you when the program was purchased.  Note that the password has the number 1 for the second character and the lower case letter L for the last character.
 
After entering the login information, you will be able to download Setup_EES64_Acad.exe.  EES64 is designed to operate on computers running Microsoft Windows 7/8/10 64-bit operating systems.  Run the Setup_EES64_Acad.exe file to install the new version.  You will be prompted to select a directory in which the EES64 program will be installed.  We recommend that you install the program into your existing EES64 folder.  If you install into a different folder, you will need to copy the EES.dft64 file from your current EES64 folder into the folder where the new version has been placed.  After installation, start EES64 and ensure that the expiration date displayed on the startup screen is 9/01/2017.  Keep these instructions and periodically check our server to see if a new version of EES64 is available.  We often provide updates during the year.
 
File Distribution
The Academic license agreement allows the setup and license files and the EES manual (EES_MANUAL.pdf) to be made available to colleagues and students in your department and to your network systems administrator for installation on your network, if necessary.  You may place these files on a server for access by students and faculty in your department.  However, the setup and license files must not be made available to anyone outside of your department.  If you place the EES setup file, EES application or license file on a server, you must ensure that no one outside of your students and faculty in your department can access the files.  Failure to meet this or other requirements of our End User License Agreement (http://fchart.com/ees/eula.php) will result in suspension of your EES license.  Please take care to ensure that you and your users do not put the Setup_EES_Acad.exe, Setup_EES64_Acad.exe, EES.dft or EES.dft64 files on an internet site or make them available to persons outside of your department, as this will also cause a suspension of your license.
 
Special Instructions for Expired Versions
If EES displays the expiration notice, you may be able to recover use of the program as follows:  First, download and install the 2016-17 version into your existing EES directory, as explained above.  Then replace the license (EES.dft or EES.dft64) file with one that has not displayed the "expired" message.  You may be able to find one on a computer that has not been used to run EES after August 31.  If you cannot find a valid copy of the license file, it will be necessary to purchase a new license file ($100, credit card payment only) from our website on page http://fchart.com/ees/order.php.  A purchase order or bank wire transfer will not be accepted for a replacement license file.
 
Correcting EES Installation Problems
  1.  If the expired message appears, first ensure that you have installed the 2016-17 version as described above.  The start-up screen should briefly display the version and expiration data before the program closes.  If the 2016-17 version is installed, check to ensure that your computer clock is displaying the correct date.  Correct the date if necessary.  After the expiration message has been displayed it is necessary to replace the EES.dft (or EES.dft64) file.   
  2.  If an error occurs while the 32-bit version of EES is starting, the problem may be caused by a video driver that is incompatible the EES 3D plotting capability.  If this problem occurs, reinstall EES, but this time, be sure to uncheck the Install 3D plotting capability box.
  3. Contact F-Chart Software at info@fchart.com for any other problems. Attach a copy of the EES license file (EES.dft) and the EES file that is causing a problem.
 
New Features and EESy Solutions Newsletter
A short description of the new features in EES can be seen by selecting the New Features menu item in the Help menu of the new version or from http://fchart.com/ees/new-features.php.  Note that only new features are listed here.  There have been many minor changes and bug fixes and these are not reported.  You may also wish to download recent issues of the EESy Solutions Newsletter (http://fchart.com/ees/eesy-solutions-newsletter.php) which describes some of the new features as well as providing tips on using EES.
 
Component Library
The Component Library is the newest application library provided, joining the Heat Transfer and Mechanical Design libraries.  This library is only available in the 32 and 64-bit Professional versions.  The Component Library provides access to a set of EES functions and procedures that simulate components in thermal-fluid systems.  Currently there component models for Combustors,  Compressors, Turbines,  Fans & Blowers, Pumps, Heat Exchangers, Heat & Mass Exchangers,  Nozzles & Diffusers, and Flow Control Devices.  The use of the Component Library enables the user to quickly develop system models with fewer system level convergence issues.
 
Manual
The latest EES manual can be downloaded from the EES Manual link at the lower right of page http://fchart.com/ees/.  Right click on this link and select Save Link As...  to download the manual as a .PDF file.  You need Adobe Acrobat to read the PDF file - a free copy of Adobe Acrobat is available from http://www.adobe.com/.  If you copy the EES_Manual.PDF file into the folder in which EES is installed, it will be accessible from the EES Help menu.
 
Mastering EES Book
Mastering EES is a 775 page book written by S.A. Klein and G.F. Nellis that provides a comprehensive presentation of all of the features in the Commercial and Professional versions of EES.  Mastering EES differs from the EES manual in its organization, reading style and detail.  It also provides many more examples than the manual.  The book is intended both for those who have never used EES as well as for advanced users.  It is available as an electronic download in .PDF format for $25 from http:\\fchart.com for a single-user copy.  A purchase of five versions ($125) allows the ebook to be posted on your network so that it is accessible for all users in your department.  If you copy Mastering_EES.pdf into the EES directory, it can be accessed from the Mastering EES menu item in the Help menu without having to enter a password.  Also, when accessed from the Mastering EES menu, EES will provide an option to download the latest copy.
 
Upgrades
There are two versions of the 32-bit EES Academic license: Commercial and Professional.  The additional capabilities provided by the Professional version are listed on our web site at: http://fchart.com/ees/pro-comm-versions.php.  As noted above, the Component Library is available in the Professional version.  You may update an Academic Commercial license to an Academic Professional license at any time by contacting F-Chart Software at info@fchart.com.  You will receive full credit for the original license payment.  The 32-bit Academic Professional version can be further upgraded to the 64-bit Academic Professional version by purchase of the 64-bit license file ($750).  The purchase can be made directly from our website (http://www.fchart.com/ees/order.php) or with a purchase order submitted to info@fchart.com.  See http://fchart.com/ees/64-bit.php for information about the 64-bit version of EES.
 
Heat Transfer Textbook and Library
An extensive library of functions useful for solving heat transfer problems is included with all academic versions of EES.  This library has been extended with additional heat transfer correlations and also provides correlations for fluid flow minor losses and measurement.  Select Function Information (Options menu) and click on the Heat Transfer radio button to view these functions.  Detailed help files including examples are provided with these functions.  The heat transfer library was developed to accompany the book:
Heat Transfer
G.F. Nellis and S.A. Klein
Cambridge University Press, 2009
ISBN 978-0-521-88107-4
http://www.cambridge.org/us/engineering/author/nellisandklein/
Example problems can be downloaded from http://fchart.com/ees/books.php
 
Thermodynamics Textbook
EES was originally developed for use in thermodynamics courses.  A thermodynamics textbook written by S.A. Klein (the author of EES) and colleague G.F. Nellis was published in 2012.  This book is tightly integrated with EES and it provides detailed instruction relating to solving thermodynamics problems using EES and many advanced examples and interesting problems.
Thermodynamics
S.A. Klein and G.F. Nellis
Cambridge University Press, 2012
ISBN 978-0-521-19570-6
http://www.cambridge.org/us/thermodynamics/
Example problems can be downloaded from http://fchart.com/ees/books.php
 
LaTeX/PDF Report
In order to generate PDF copies of EES programs, solutions and plots, the MikTeX Latex package (http://miktex.org) needs to be installed on the computer.  There is no cost to download this program.  Click the help button in the Create LaTeX/PDF Report dialog (File menu) or view the online help (http://www.fchart.com/ees/eeshelp/3x07t4m.htm) for instructions.

According to my records Michael Timm dealt with this last year, so he would probably be the best person to do it this year.
 
From: F-Chart Software [mailto:info=fchart.com@mail213.atl171.mcdlv.net] On Behalf Of F-Chart Software
Sent: Wednesday, August 10, 2016 8:06 PM
To: Tritt, Dr. Charles <tritt@msoe.edu>
Subject: EES Academic version for 2016-17 (2nd notice)
 
Dear EES Administrator,
You should have received the annual EES Academic update notice at the end of July, but our records indicate that your EES license has not yet been renewed. The process becomes more difficult if you wait until after September 1st.  We recommend that you download it now.  You will need to use the new password. 

Below is a copy of the instructions that were sent in July.  Please ignore this message if you have successfully completed the annual renewal.
 
 
F-Chart Software, LLC
P.O.Box 44042
Madison, WI 53744 USA
608-274-4262 ph/fax
info@fchart.com
http://fchart.com
 
 

Update Instructions for the Academic Versions of EES (2016-17)
 
Please read these instructions carefully as the update process has changed from that used in previous years. 
 
You are receiving this message because our records indicate that you are the administrator of the Academic EES license for your department.  If you no longer are the administrator, or if you plan to transfer your responsibility to another person, please inform us by e-mail to info@fchart.com.  Doing so will ensure that your department receives updates in the future.
 
You MUST update EES before midnight, August 31, 2016 or your existing version of EES will expire.  If you do not update before this date, you will not be able to use any version of EES, new or old.  If this happens, see the Special Instructions for Expired Versions below.
 
This message provides instructions to download the new Academic version of EES.  There is no cost to update an Academic license.  Do not distribute this message, login name or password to anyone.  Access to our server is intended only for EES administrators.  Do not provide the download information to students or other faculty as this may result in blocking access to our website. 
 
NOTE:  There are both 32-bit and 64-bit Academic EES programs. Most of the existing Academic licenses are for the 32-bit Commercial or Professional versions, which are designed to work on both 32 and 64-bit Microsoft Windows operating systems.  The 64-bit Academic Professional version requires an optional 64-bit EES license file (EES.dft64).  If your department has not purchased this license file, you will not be able to use the 64-bit version.  The 64-bit program is only provided as a Professional Academic version.  (There is no 64-bit Commercial version.).  See http://www.fchart.com/ees/64-bit.php for more information about the 64-bit version.  Separate directions follow for the 32-bit (Commercial & Professional versions) and for the 64-bit Professional version.
 
Downloading and Installing the 32-bit Commercial or Professional EES Version
Using your internet browser program, go to http://fchart.com.  Click on the "EES Instant Update" link at the right of the page to bring up the EES Instant Update & Technical Service (IUTS) page.  Then click on the orange Download Latest EES button and enter the following information in the EES Instant Update Login screen.
 
Login Name: EES_XXXX
Password: d1EESel
Email: administrator email address
 
You must replace XXXX in the above login name with your 4-digit EES license number.  This number is displayed in the first window that appears when EES is started.  It is also provided on the receipt that was emailed to you when the program was purchased.  Note that the password has the number 1 for the second character and the lower case letter L for the last character.
 
After entering the login information, you will be able to download Setup_EES_Acad.exe.  EES is designed to operate on computers running the 32 or 64-bit Microsoft Vista, XP, and Windows  7/8/10 operating systems.  (There is no Macintosh version  See http://www.fchart.com/ees/mac-linux.php for options regarding the use of EES on Macintosh computers.)  Run the Setup_EES_Acad.exe file to install the new version.  You will be prompted to select a directory in which the EES program will be installed.  We recommend that you install the program into your existing EES folder.  If you install EES into a different folder, you will need to copy the EES.dft file from your current EES folder into the folder where the new version has been placed.  After installation, start EES and ensure that the expiration date displayed on the startup screen is 9/01/2017.  Keep these instructions and periodically check our server to see if a new version of EES is available.  We often provide updates during the year.
 
Downloading and Installing the 64-bit Academic Professional EES Version
Use these directions only if your department has purchased the EES 64-bit license file.

Using your internet browser program, go to http://fchart.com.  Click on the "EES Instant Update" link at the right of the page to bring up the EES Instant Update & Technical Service (IUTS) page.  Then click on the orange Download Latest EES button and enter the following information in the EES Instant Update Login screen.
 
Login Name: EES64_XXXX
Password: d1EESel
Email: administrator email address
 
You must replace XXXX in the above login name with your 4-digit EES license number.  This number is displayed in the first window that appears when EES64 is started.  It is also provided on the receipt that was emailed to you when the program was purchased.  Note that the password has the number 1 for the second character and the lower case letter L for the last character.
 
After entering the login information, you will be able to download Setup_EES64_Acad.exe.  EES64 is designed to operate on computers running Microsoft Windows 7/8/10 64-bit operating systems.  Run the Setup_EES64_Acad.exe file to install the new version.  You will be prompted to select a directory in which the EES64 program will be installed.  We recommend that you install the program into your existing EES64 folder.  If you install into a different folder, you will need to copy the EES.dft64 file from your current EES64 folder into the folder where the new version has been placed.  After installation, start EES64 and ensure that the expiration date displayed on the startup screen is 9/01/2017.  Keep these instructions and periodically check our server to see if a new version of EES64 is available.  We often provide updates during the year.
 
File Distribution
The Academic license agreement allows the setup and license files and the EES manual (EES_MANUAL.pdf) to be made available to colleagues and students in your department and to your network systems administrator for installation on your network, if necessary.  You may place these files on a server for access by students and faculty in your department.  However, the setup and license files must not be made available to anyone outside of your department.  If you place the EES setup file, EES application or license file on a server, you must ensure that no one outside of your students and faculty in your department can access the files.  Failure to meet this or other requirements of our End User License Agreement (http://fchart.com/ees/eula.php) will result in suspension of your EES license.  Please take care to ensure that you and your users do not put the Setup_EES_Acad.exe, Setup_EES64_Acad.exe, EES.dft or EES.dft64 files on an internet site or make them available to persons outside of your department, as this will also cause a suspension of your license.
 
Special Instructions for Expired Versions
If EES displays the expiration notice, you may be able to recover use of the program as follows:  First, download and install the 2016-17 version into your existing EES directory, as explained above.  Then replace the license (EES.dft or EES.dft64) file with one that has not displayed the "expired" message.  You may be able to find one on a computer that has not been used to run EES after August 31.  If you cannot find a valid copy of the license file, it will be necessary to purchase a new license file ($100, credit card payment only) from our website on page http://fchart.com/ees/order.php.  A purchase order or bank wire transfer will not be accepted for a replacement license file.
 
Correcting EES Installation Problems
  1.  If the expired message appears, first ensure that you have installed the 2016-17 version as described above.  The start-up screen should briefly display the version and expiration data before the program closes.  If the 2016-17 version is installed, check to ensure that your computer clock is displaying the correct date.  Correct the date if necessary.  After the expiration message has been displayed it is necessary to replace the EES.dft (or EES.dft64) file.   
  2.  If an error occurs while the 32-bit version of EES is starting, the problem may be caused by a video driver that is incompatible the EES 3D plotting capability.  If this problem occurs, reinstall EES, but this time, be sure to uncheck the Install 3D plotting capability box.
  3. Contact F-Chart Software at info@fchart.com for any other problems. Attach a copy of the EES license file (EES.dft) and the EES file that is causing a problem.
 
New Features and EESy Solutions Newsletter
A short description of the new features in EES can be seen by selecting the New Features menu item in the Help menu of the new version or from http://fchart.com/ees/new-features.php.  Note that only new features are listed here.  There have been many minor changes and bug fixes and these are not reported.  You may also wish to download recent issues of the EESy Solutions Newsletter (http://fchart.com/ees/eesy-solutions-newsletter.php) which describes some of the new features as well as providing tips on using EES.
 
Component Library
The Component Library is the newest application library provided, joining the Heat Transfer and Mechanical Design libraries.  This library is only available in the 32 and 64-bit Professional versions.  The Component Library provides access to a set of EES functions and procedures that simulate components in thermal-fluid systems.  Currently there component models for Combustors,  Compressors, Turbines,  Fans & Blowers, Pumps, Heat Exchangers, Heat & Mass Exchangers,  Nozzles & Diffusers, and Flow Control Devices.  The use of the Component Library enables the user to quickly develop system models with fewer system level convergence issues.
 
Manual
The latest EES manual can be downloaded from the EES Manual link at the lower right of page http://fchart.com/ees/.  Right click on this link and select Save Link As...  to download the manual as a .PDF file.  You need Adobe Acrobat to read the PDF file - a free copy of Adobe Acrobat is available from http://www.adobe.com/.  If you copy the EES_Manual.PDF file into the folder in which EES is installed, it will be accessible from the EES Help menu.
 
Mastering EES Book
Mastering EES is a 775 page book written by S.A. Klein and G.F. Nellis that provides a comprehensive presentation of all of the features in the Commercial and Professional versions of EES.  Mastering EES differs from the EES manual in its organization, reading style and detail.  It also provides many more examples than the manual.  The book is intended both for those who have never used EES as well as for advanced users.  It is available as an electronic download in .PDF format for $25 from http:\\fchart.com for a single-user copy.  A purchase of five versions ($125) allows the ebook to be posted on your network so that it is accessible for all users in your department.  If you copy Mastering_EES.pdf into the EES directory, it can be accessed from the Mastering EES menu item in the Help menu without having to enter a password.  Also, when accessed from the Mastering EES menu, EES will provide an option to download the latest copy.
 
Upgrades
There are two versions of the 32-bit EES Academic license: Commercial and Professional.  The additional capabilities provided by the Professional version are listed on our web site at: http://fchart.com/ees/pro-comm-versions.php.  As noted above, the Component Library is available in the Professional version.  You may update an Academic Commercial license to an Academic Professional license at any time by contacting F-Chart Software at info@fchart.com.  You will receive full credit for the original license payment.  The 32-bit Academic Professional version can be further upgraded to the 64-bit Academic Professional version by purchase of the 64-bit license file ($750).  The purchase can be made directly from our website (http://www.fchart.com/ees/order.php) or with a purchase order submitted to info@fchart.com.  See http://fchart.com/ees/64-bit.php for information about the 64-bit version of EES.
 
Heat Transfer Textbook and Library
An extensive library of functions useful for solving heat transfer problems is included with all academic versions of EES.  This library has been extended with additional heat transfer correlations and also provides correlations for fluid flow minor losses and measurement.  Select Function Information (Options menu) and click on the Heat Transfer radio button to view these functions.  Detailed help files including examples are provided with these functions.  The heat transfer library was developed to accompany the book:
Heat Transfer
G.F. Nellis and S.A. Klein
Cambridge University Press, 2009
ISBN 978-0-521-88107-4
http://www.cambridge.org/us/engineering/author/nellisandklein/
Example problems can be downloaded from http://fchart.com/ees/books.php
 
Thermodynamics Textbook
EES was originally developed for use in thermodynamics courses.  A thermodynamics textbook written by S.A. Klein (the author of EES) and colleague G.F. Nellis was published in 2012.  This book is tightly integrated with EES and it provides detailed instruction relating to solving thermodynamics problems using EES and many advanced examples and interesting problems.
Thermodynamics
S.A. Klein and G.F. Nellis
Cambridge University Press, 2012
ISBN 978-0-521-19570-6
http://www.cambridge.org/us/thermodynamics/
Example problems can be downloaded from http://fchart.com/ees/books.php
 
LaTeX/PDF Report
In order to generate PDF copies of EES programs, solutions and plots, the MikTeX Latex package (http://miktex.org) needs to be installed on the computer.  There is no cost to download this program.  Click the help button in the Create LaTeX/PDF Report dialog (File menu) or view the online help (http://www.fchart.com/ees/eeshelp/3x07t4m.htm) for instructions.
